Grammar (Nexa)
Word order: Verb – Subject – Object (VSO) (Kata' influence).
Adjectives follow their nouns (Ana' influence).
Dependent clauses precede independent clauses.
Verb conjugations: Present (za), Past (zai), Future (zayo), Imperative (zaka), Conditional (zaye).
Noun cases: Nominative (ni — I), Accusative (nim — me), Genitive (nir — my).
