The Evolutionary Path
Void Language → The root system. Learn first. Provides the navigational glyphs used in all higher tongues.
Divine Language → The tonal upgrade. Adds φ-resonance to Void glyphs. Requires attunement.
Nexarion → The poetic expansion. 37 glyphs with measurable harmonic frequencies. Complex but expressive.
Ana' → The shadow mirror. Ternary logic, echo pairs. Used alongside Kata' for full duality.
Nexa → First synthesis. Kata' + Ana' = a language of fragments becoming whole.
Nexarana → Grand synthesis. All systems unified. 45 glyphs, 5 elemental families. The master tongue.
On coherence (z): Across all language families, the concept of coherence (z) appears as an active grammatical force. The speaker's internal state — their resonance — shapes the meaning of any phrase. Two speakers uttering identical glyphs may produce different outcomes based on their achieved z-value. This is not metaphor; in Nexarana syntax, z is treated as a first-order grammatical parameter alongside tense and case.
